A WalkAnimMoveSpeed of 3 means the unit is animated to walk at a rate of 3 tiles per second in the default case.  (The artist creating the asset actually types a value that is 100 times this into the asset in MAX, because in that context, a tile is 100 inches.)

EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Chance=Specifies a percentage chance that a sound will actually create a voice when you request to play it. Defaults to 100%.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_ConeAngle=Configures the FMOD channel cone parameters. Only applicable to 3D sounds; relative to the sound position in the world.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_ConeOrientation=Configures the FMOD channel cone parameters. Only applicable to 3D sounds; relative to the sound position in the world.

EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeDestroyCount=Specifies the maximum instances of a sound that may be created before the least important voice is destroyed or when we stop creating new sounds (depends on the dupe maximum method).
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeFadeBlend=Specifies a fade curve to use when a voice becomes or is no longer considered a duplicate.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeFadeIn=Specifies a fade curve to use when a voice becomes a duplicate.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeFadeOut=Specifies a fade curve to use when a voice is no longer considered a duplicate.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeHistoryCount=Specifies how many instances we track of a sound when it is done playing. Used primarily for sound selection when playing a new sound. For Random, we use the history to determine the last sound that played so we can avoid repeating that one.  For Shuffle, we use the history to find the least played subset and do a weighted randomization to select between them.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeMaximumMethod=Specifies how the sound engine handles the situation when the maximum number of duplicate sounds have been played.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeMuteCount=Specifies how many instances of a sound that may be created before the least important voice is muted.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupePrioritization=This determines the order that duplicate sounds are destroyed in.  Default = mixer priority, distance, audibility.  Oldest = Oldest Destroyed First.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeRepeatCount=Specifies how many repeated instances of a specific asset are permitted, even if they aren't overlapping. The least important instances beyond this count will be silenced.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeThresholdFadeTime=Specifies the fading behavior when a threshold of sounds for a category has been reached or is no longer present.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeThresholdPoints=Specifies the fading behavior when a threshold of sounds for a category has been reached or is no longer present.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_DupeWait=Specifies how long after a sound is played before another is allowed to play in its audible range. Primarily used for creep sounds. This value may be randomized by picking a lower and upper bounds.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_EditorCategories=Editor Categories are used for filtering and organization within the StarCraft II Editor.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Exclusivity=Determines whether this sound can be prevented from playing, or delayed, due to other sounds currently being played.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Flags=Configures various options for the sound.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_FogFadeBlend=Specifies the fade curve to use when a 3D sound becomes fogged or unfogged.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_FogFadeIn=Specifies the fade curve to use when a 3D sound becomes unfogged.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_FogFadeOut=Specifies the fade curve to use when a 3D sound becomes fogged.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_LocaleFlags=Only used by the editor to indicate production tracking status on localization.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_LocalVolumeAdjustment=Applies a volume adjustment when the sound is played owned by the local player.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_LoopCount=Specifies the number of times that a sound set will repeat. This will cause it to loop over all available assets based on their selection mode (shuffle or sequential). Specify -1 here to indicate you want it to loop infinitely. Note that loop points need to be configured per-asset, if applicable.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_LowPassGain=Configures the FMOD channel low pass gain parameter (sets the gain of the dry signal when lowpass filtering is applied).
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_MixerPriority=A sound with a higher priority than another sound will not be stolen or made virtual by that sound. 0 = most important. 256 = least important. A value of -1 means to use the mixer priority of the sound category for this sound.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_MixerPriorityNonLocal=Mixer priority to use for non local sounds. A value of -1 means to use the same priority as local sounds.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Mode=Indicates if the sound should be configured as 2D, 3D (Head Relative), or 3D (World Relative). Sounds that are configured as 2D do not have a fog test performed. Generally 2D sounds should be reserved to map-wide audio like the ambience soundtrack or UI sounds. If a sound is configured as a 3D world-relative sound but does not have a valid position, it will be converted to a 3D head-relative sound.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_MuteFadeBlend=Specifies the fade behavior when a sound is muted or unmuted.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_MuteFadeIn=Specifies the fade behavior when a sound is muted.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_MuteFadeOut=Specifies the fade behavior when a sound is unmuted.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_NonLocalVolumeAdjustment=Applies a volume adjustment when the sound is played not owned by the local player.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OcclusionDirect=Configures the occlusion factors for a channel. Only applicable to 3D sounds. We don't have FMOD geometry objects, so this is the only way to reproduce that kind of behavior. This value may be randomized by picking a lower and upper bounds.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OcclusionReverb=Configures the occlusion factors for a channel. Only applicable to 3D sounds. We don't have FMOD geometry objects, so this is the only way to reproduce that kind of behavior. This value may be randomized by picking a lower and upper bounds.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OffsetFadeBlend=Specifies the fade in and fade out curve for a sound. The times are relative to the overall sound length including looping.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OffsetFadeIn=Specifies the fade in curve for a sound. The times are relative to the overall sound length including looping.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OffsetFadeOut=Specifies the fade out curve for a sound. The times are relative to the overall sound length including looping.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OffsetShiftBlend=Specifies the pitch shift in and out curve for a sound. The times are relative to the overall sound length including looping.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OffsetShiftIn=Specifies the pitch shift in curve for a sound. The times are relative to the overall sound length including looping.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OffsetShiftOut=Specifies the pitch shift out curve for a sound. The times are relative to the overall sound length including looping.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OverlapPitchDelta=Specifies the threshold for comparing two instances of the same asset to determine if they are overlapping (in which case the least important sounds are muted). Note that the pitch value refers to the Pitch data value, not the actual pitch of the waveform.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_OverlapTimeDelta=Specifies the threshold for comparing two instances of the same asset to determine if they are overlapping (in which case the least important sounds are muted). Note that the pitch value refers to the Pitch data value, not the actual pitch of the waveform.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Pan=Specifies the speaker pan amount for 2D sounds. -1 = full left, +1 = full right, 0 = center. Defaults to 0. This value may be randomized by picking a lower and upper bounds.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_PanLevel=Configures the FMOD channel 3D pan level parameter (sets how much the 3d engine has an effect on the channel, versus that set by Pan or Speaker Mix).  0 is 100% using the Speaker Mix values and not using the 3D engine at all.  1 is 100% using the 3D engine and not using the Speaker Mix values at all.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_PanLevelNonLocal=The pan level to use for non local sounds. Less than zero means to use the value in pan level.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Pitch=Specifies a frequency shift for the sound. This is not a true octave shift, although there is a DSP (which is expensive) that can be applied to accomplish that. This value may be randomized by picking a lower and upper bounds.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_PlayDelay=How long to delay playing this sound (in ms)
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_PositionRandomOffset=The position of the sound will be randomly offset by up to this amount either positively or negatively.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_PositionRandomOffsetPower=This is used to modify the distribution of the random offset.  The percentage offset on each axis (0..1) is taken to this power.  Less than 1 means that points will tend to be more towards the edges.  Greater than one 1 means the points will tend to be more towards the center.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_ResourcePriority=Used by the resource management system to determine how important this sound is to load and keep in memory.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_ReverbBalance=Configures the default reverb direct and room levels.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_ReverbRolloffBlend=Controls how much the default reverb levels are affected by a sound's distance from the listener.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_ReverbRolloffPoints=Controls how much the default reverb levels are affected by a sound's distance from the listener.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Select=Specifies the way that we cycle through sounds in a set when looping over all assets or playing multiple instances of the same sound. Sequential means that we will play each of the assets in the sound before repeating. Shuffle means that we will randomly select assets until all of the assets have been played and then we will choose a new playlist. The same sound will never play back-to-back unless there is only one asset, or the same asset is in the set multiple times.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_SpeakerMix=Configures the FMOD channel speaker mix per speaker. The most commonly adjusted setting here is adjusting the LFE volume for 3D sounds.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_SpeakerMixNonLocal=The speaker mix to use if this sound is played for a non local player. -1 means to use the value in SpeakerMix.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Spread=Configures the FMOD channel 3D spread setting in speaker space. When increasing the spread of a sound, the left and right parts of a stereo sound rotate away from their original position to give it more "stereoness".  Mono sounds can also be "spread" with this parameter.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_SustainFade=Specifies the fade behavior when a sound is interrupted (usually by scripts or other gameplay).
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_SustainFadeBlend=Specifies the fade behavior when a sound is interrupted (usually by scripts or other gameplay).
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Timeout=Specifies the amount of time that we wait for a sound to load (and maybe download) before we give up and cancel the request. Useful for making sure sounds don't play long after they are relevant.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_VariationMinimum=Specifies the minimum number of assets from a sound that must be available regardless of the sound quality setting in the sound options panel.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_Volume=Configures the ideal volume of a sound without any mixing or fading applied. This value may be randomized by picking a lower and upper bounds. This value is multiplied by the per-asset volume.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_VolumeRolloffBlend=Specifies the volume adjustment behavior for 3D sounds based on the listener position. 
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_VolumeRolloffFadeBlend=Specifies the volume adjustment behavior for 3D sounds based on the listener position. 
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_VolumeRolloffFadeIn=Specifies the volume adjustment behavior for 3D sounds based on the listener position. 
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_VolumeRolloffFadeOut=Specifies the volume adjustment behavior for 3D sounds based on the listener position. 
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSound_VolumeRolloffPoints=Specifies the volume adjustment behavior for 3D sounds based on the listener position. 
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_CollideWithEqual=What action to take if an equal priority sound is already playing when the sound wants to play.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_CollideWithHigher=What action to take if a higher priority sound is already playing when the sound wants to play.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_CollideWithLower=What action to take if a lower priority sound is already playing when the sound wants to play.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_DupeWait=Prevent a sound using this exclusivity record from playing within this amount of time.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_Group=The exclusivity group of the sound.  All sounds played using this group will consider each other for exclusivity.  Sounds from other groups, or who don't have any group, will not be considered for exclusivity tests.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_InterruptDelay=If this sound is interrupted, the sound interrupting it will delay it's playback by this amount to allow this sound to fade out etc.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_InterruptFade=If this sound is interrupted, it will blend out using this setting.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_InterruptFadeBlend=If this sound is interrupted, it will blend out using this setting.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_Priority=The priority within the exclusivity group.  Used to make decisions about which sounds are more important than others.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_QCollideWithEqual=What action to take if an equal priority sound is already queued when the sound wants to enter the queue.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_QCollideWithHigher=What action to take if a higher priority sound is already queued when the sound wants to enter the queue.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_QCollideWithLower=What action to take if a lower priority sound is already queued when the sound wants to enter the queue.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_QDelay=When a sound is dequeued, it will wait this long (in ms) before playing.  This delay does not count towards the queue timeout time.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_QTimeout=If the sound is queued for longer than this amount of time (in ms), it will give up and leave the queue without playing. A value of zero means it will never time out.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundExclusivity_SuppressGroups=When a sound plays using this exclusivity data record, it will suppress these group numbers for ALL owning players.  Sounds in those groups will not be able to be played again until this sound is finished, and if the SupressionInterrupts flag is set, currently playing sounds will be interrupted.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundMixSnapshot_Attack=How long it should take to fully apply the sound mix (milliseconds)
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundMixSnapshot_Hold=How long to apply the sound mix for (milliseconds)
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundMixSnapshot_MixGlobal=Global Sound Mix Snapshot
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundMixSnapshot_MixNonLocal=Non Local Sound Mix Snapshot
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundMixSnapshot_Release=How long it should take to unapply the sound mix (milliseconds)
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundtrack_CueArray=Cue parameters for each sound in the soundtrack. These parameters also let you add tracks to the soundtrack.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundtrack_Delay=Delay time between songs in the soundtrack
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundtrack_Flags=Flags for the soundtrack item.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CSoundtrack_Select=Order in which the game selects sounds from the soundtrack
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CTacticalOrder_Abil=Ability order issued to the unit by the tactical order.

EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CUnit_Acceleration=Rate of speed increase at which the unit reaches maximum speed

EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CUnit_AIEvalConstant=Specifies a flat value to be added to the AI importance calculation.

EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CUnit_AINotifyEffect=Notification effect that occurs for the unit
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CUnit_AIOverideTargetPriority=Priority for the unit that is used when the attacking unit is controlled by an AI player. When one unit has a higher priority than other units, the higher priority unit is attacked first.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CUnit_AttackSpeedMultiplierCreep=Increases the attack speed while on creep by multiplying this value by any other attack speed multipliers.

EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CUnit_Attributes=Attributes for the unit. These attributes determine how weapons and armor affect the unit.
EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CUnit_BehaviorArray=Any behaviors added to the unit in this field are automatically applied to the unit when it is created. Behaviors can modify most of the inherent attributes of a unit including movement speed, armor values, and cloaking/detection.

EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CUnit_CardLayouts=The command card for each unit defines a set of buttons for that unit to be displayed when that unit is selected, typically as a grid in the bottom right of the screen. The buttons displayed here can be used to activate or target an ability like Attack or Stim Pack, but can also be used for other purposes like temporarily switching the command card to a different 'card' of buttons or for displaying a button for a passive behavior on that unit.

EDSTR_FIELDHINT_CUnit_OverlapIndex=This value determines what other units it may overlap with while moving. The index can be 0, 1, or 2. 0 means that the unit cannot overlap with other units. A unit set to 1 and another unit set to 2 can overlap with eachother. 1 cannot overlap with another 1, and 2 cannot overlap with another 2. If two units are allowed to overlap, then the center points of those units must be X distance away, where X is the smaller of two those units' radii. If the two units cannot overlap, then the center points of those units must be Y distance away, where Y is both of their radii added together.

This is not exact for gib-style ragdolls where pieces fly everywhere, because the player might see a body part with a body squib model that does not have an associated sound, and conversely, he might see a body part with no body squib that plays a body squib sound.  But in most cases it fairly accurate and it is hard to notice when it is not, so this technique is typically good enough.
